# Research Link Tracking

When performing web research (using WebSearch, WebFetch, or citing external sources), save the best links to `RESEARCH_LINKS.md` in the project root.

## When to Log

- After any web search that yields useful results
- When referencing external documentation, articles, or resources

## What to Log

- The **1–5 best links** from each research activity
- A short description of what was being researched and why

## Format

```markdown
## YYYY-MM-DD — Research topic

**Context**: 1 sentence on why this was researched.

| # | Link | Description |
|---|------|-------------|
| 1 | URL  | What this resource covers |
```

## Rules

- New entries go at the top of the file (newest first), below the heading.
- If `RESEARCH_LINKS.md` does not exist yet, create it with a top-level `# Research Links` heading.
- Do not duplicate entries — if the same link was already logged, skip it.
- Always present the 1–5 best links to the user in the chat response as well.
- Keep descriptions concise (one sentence max per link).
